        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:06PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 305 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a slow-moving thunderstorm
near Cedar Rapids. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Minor flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Slowing or redirecting of traffic due to ponding or flowing
water. Closure of waterfront access due to flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Cedar Rapids, Marion, Ely, Swisher, Shueyville, Bertram,
Palisades-Kepler State Park, Cou Falls, Cedar Rapids Municipal
Airport, and Squaw Creek Park.

This includes Interstate 380 between mile markers 9 and 18.

Rainfall amounts of around 1 inch have fallen and an additional 1
to 2 inches of rain are possible.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring and may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Stay away from
flooded areas. Report any flooding to local law enforcement.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
